stylometry: The broad and general mangement tradeoff and decision you face when managing inventory is when to place an order and how much you need to cover the demand with not having holding costs go through the roof. If you order to much you can run into having extremely high holding cost because it will not all sell within the time period you plan on. But if you order to little then you will not have enough to meet the demand of your customers and then you will have unhappy customers and could loose sales. So  you have to try and plan accordingly so you have enough inventory to meet the demand while still being able to minimize your holding costs. You also have to manage how many times you order inventory because their is ordering costs, this is why not every company can run on a just in time basis. It gets expensive to order as you need it.
